  "unit": {
    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Two structures. Adverbs of manner (revision): adjective→adverb (+-ly, -y→-ily happy/happily, -le→-ly gentle/gently; irregular good→well, fast→fast, hard→hard), position after verb/object, adverb-vs-adjective, linking verbs (taste/feel/look) take the adjective. Question tags: positive statement→negative tag / negative→positive; tag repeats the auxiliary/modal (do-support where none); tag pronoun matches the subject. 18 vocab + 112 grammar (2 structures, floor 40 each → 58 + 54), full v1 parity. 4 verify lenses clean after fixes: the answers lens vetted BOTH structures (every -ly form, polarity, auxiliary, pronoun, and the special cases aren't I / shall we / won't it correct) and translation found 0 defects; relabeled both question-tag group-sorts off German labels (ja-Satz/nein-Satz/Eigenschaftswort → tag-exemplar labels 'isn't it?'/'is it?' and 'do/does/did'/'is/are/can/has'); reworded 3 'Eigenschaftswort' prompts → functional ('ein Wort wie good/bad, kein -ly-Wort'); swapped the too-valid 'well'/'fast' distractors → adjectives (careful/clear/beautiful + quick/quiet) in 3 cue-less adverb MCs so they test the real adverb-vs-adjective point; disambiguated 3 translation prompts Sie→Mia/Sue; reworded the drop-out def off its headword token 'school'. Granted the -ly adverb forms + base adjectives (derivational -ly is NOT in the gate's inflection family, so every -ly adverb gates untaught). The 12 inline glosses (won't/should/shouldn't + adverbs) are correct; 27 translation audits accurate (tag→German 'oder?'/'nicht wahr?'). Two non-actionable level-gloss warns (could/couldn't unglossed — but they are gate-taught, so a gloss would be V-6-unneeded). Validate green."
